{"name": "lecroyutils", "metadata": {"name": "lecroyutils", "version": "4.0.2", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Interface Engine/Protocol Translator"], "home_page": "https://github.com/sibartel/lecroyutils", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "python-vxi11"], "summary": "Library to communicate and parse .trc files with/from LeCroy oscilloscopes.", "upload_time": 1714227411}, "documentation": ["# lecroyutils\n\n[![pypi](https://badgen.net/pypi/v/lecroyutils/)](https://pypi.org/project/lecroyutils/)\n\nLibrary to communicate and parse .trc files with/from LeCroy oscilloscopes.\n\nThis library is based on previous work:\n* File src/lecroyutils/data.py on [lecroyparser](https://github.com/bennomeier/leCroyParser)\n* File src/lecroyutils/control.py on [LecroyScope_python_snippet](https://github.com/ethz-pes/LecroyScope_python_snippet)\n\n## Features\n* remote control LeCroy oscilloscopes over vxi11\n    * does not require additional drivers (no visa)\n    * controlling trigger settings\n    * accessing statistics\n    * downloading screenshots\n    * view and donwload waveform data\n* parse LeCroy .trc waveform data\n    * support for sequence mode\n    * x and y units\n\n## Installation\n\nlecroyutils is available in the Python Package Index (PyPi). It may be installed with pip:\n\n```bash\n> pip install lecroyutils\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom lecroyutils.data import LecroyScopeData\n\n# Parse a local .trc file\ndata = LecroyScopeData.parse_file('C2_00000_Lecroy.trc')\n\nfrom lecroyutils.control import LecroyScope, TriggerMode, TriggerType\n\n# Connect to a scope over vxi11\nscope = LecroyScope('127.0.0.1')\nscope.trigger_type = TriggerType.edge\nscope.trigger_source = 'C1'\nscope.acquire(force=True)\ndata = scope.waveform('C1')\n\nscope.save_waveform('C1', 'C1_00000_Lecroy.trc')\n```\n\n## Related\n* [lecroyparser](https://github.com/bennomeier/leCroyParser)\n* [LecroyScope_python_snippet](https://github.com/ethz-pes/LecroyScope_python_snippet)\n* [python-vxi11](https://github.com/python-ivi/python-vxi11)\n\n## License\nlecroyutils is licensed under the [MIT](LICENSE) license.\n\n## Notice\nWe are not affiliated, associated, authorized, endorsed by, or in any way officially connected with Teledyne LeCroy, or any of its subsidiaries or its affiliates. The official Teledyne LeCroy github profile can be found at https://github.com/TeledyneLeCroy.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "lecroyutils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "lecroyutils.data.DataCorruptException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The provided data is corrupt and therefore not parsable."]}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData.parse_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "*kargs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "LecroyScopeData", "xref": {"fqname": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Reads the provided file and parses the data as `LecroyScopeData`.\n\nThe `LecroyScopeData.source_desc` is set to the provided filepath in the\nreturned `LecroyScopeData` instance.\n\n```\nparam filepath\n\nfile to read\n\nparam kargs\n\narguments are directly passed to \n\nparam kwargs\n\narguments are directly passed to \n\nreturn\n\n instance\n```\n"]}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "AnyStr", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AnyStr", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sparse", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "source_desc", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Parse the provided `data` as waveform data from a lecroy oscilloscope.\n\n```\nparam data\n\nthe data to be parsed\n\nparam sparse\n\nif set the waveform data is sparse decoded\n\nparam source_desc\n\ncan be used to track the origin of the provided data\n```\n"]}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData._unpack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pos", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "format_specifier", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "length", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData._parse_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pos", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "length", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData._parse_int16", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pos", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lecroyutils.data.LecroyScopeData._parse_word", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pos", "type": null, "default": null}